The paper deals with distance and routing labeling schemes for graphs, which are topics in computer science related to data structures and algorithms. Specifically, the paper focuses on cube-free median graphs, which are a type of graph that can be used to model various real-world networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, since the paper discusses the efficiency of computing distances and routing, it may also be relevant to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
